LongDescription:
Lineships form the primary fighting element of the Protectorate fleet.  Rapidly refit from seized commercial freighters and pressed into service during the blockade of the Kribensis gate.  This series of lineship is built from bulk carriers, which specialize in transporting huge quantities of loose materials.  They have been primarily refit to wield large guns along their sides, taking advantage of their cavernous internal space.

Don't let their size fool you, they are anything but lumbering.  These ships were designed to carry tens of thousands of tons of cargo, and with their holds empty their oversized engines are able to push them to speeds well beyond what would be expected of a similarly-sized warship.
FlavorText:
Constantine,

I've attached the materiel assessment to this message, take a look when you have a chance. Speaking frankly here, even with the reactivated Ocello stock, we're a little undergunned but I think with the additional numbers from Vanderburg & Sons, Stronghold Freight, and Nova's freighterline, we could put some serious hurt on the Alliance.

Most of these freighters are made-to-order but Command Engineering managed to get a relatively uniform refit across the board, so don't worry about one freighter not having something another has. They're not Axfords or Vauxhalls but with the Otdel's recent fixed guns filling the arsenal, these could pack enough firepower to keep the Alliance parked in Kribensis so long as Bulwark can keep production up.

- Amelie, Logistics Command
